<TITLE> Stocks end lower </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 02 (bdnews24.com)Stocks ended downbeat Sunday continuing the trend from the last trading day of the previous week. The market saw a steep fall in morning trade and gained slightly after midday before declining again towards the end. The DGEN or general index slumped 92.37 points or 3.1 percent to end at 2878.74. The DSI or all share price index closed at 2433.92, down 77.40 points or 3.08 percent. The DSE-20 blue chip index also declined 68.95 points or 2.95 percent ending at 2263.52. Turnover on the country's prime bourse stood at Tk 1.35 billion from trading of 8,429,980 shares, with 16 issues advancing, 181 declining and 11 holding steady. All the scrips on the top 10 shares declined. UCBL emerged first among the top 10 shares although it fell 8.35 percent to close at Tk 4716.75. The bank announced that a court order had extended a deadline to Jan 31, 2008 for holding its AGMs for the years 2003 to 2006. BRAC Bank, second in value after UCBL, closed at Tk 1538.50, down 2.59 percent. Islami Bank Perpetual Bond declined 9.21 percent to end at Tk 1485.25. Market heavyweight Power Grid Company of Bangladesh also fell 1.58 percent to Tk 683.75. Square Pharma, one of the most active shares, saw its price falling 3.02 percent to Tk 3219.50. Other scrips among the top 10 shares by valueUttara Bank, BOC Bangladesh, Grameen1 Mutual Fund, Islami Bank and Trust Bankalso fell. All the indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange also declined, with 38 issues gaining, 67 losing and 5 remaining unchanged. A total of 1,990,457 shares worth Tk 222.525 million changed hands on the bourse. bdne
